1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:01,367
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

2
00:00:01,367 --> 00:00:02,700
(Filming complied with guidelines
for children, youth, and animals.)

3
00:00:04,133 --> 00:00:08,000
A race to find the new owner
of Kangsu Group.

4
00:00:10,933 --> 00:00:14,667
Which of the three of you
will lead Kangsu Group next...

5
00:00:15,767 --> 00:00:17,133
will depend on your performance.

6
00:00:17,133 --> 00:00:19,667
Wait, Chairman.

7
00:00:19,967 --> 00:00:21,633
What exactly are you saying right now?

8
00:00:22,967 --> 00:00:24,867
The successor should obviously be...

9
00:00:25,767 --> 00:00:26,767
Obviously?

10
00:00:28,033 --> 00:00:32,267
I've worked at Kangsu Construction
for 35 years.

11
00:00:32,600 --> 00:00:34,700
I devoted my entire life
working under you.

12
00:00:35,200 --> 00:00:37,533
I'm also currently
the president of Kangsu Construction.

13
00:00:38,500 --> 00:00:40,033
So why should I have to compete
in this race?

14
00:00:40,433 --> 00:00:44,300
Do you think you got that position
solely through your own abilities?

15
00:00:45,033 --> 00:00:47,767
Then all the employees who've worked here
for over 35 years...

16
00:00:47,767 --> 00:00:50,900
should be presidents too.

17
00:00:51,233 --> 00:00:53,100
Even so, no matter how you look at it...

18
00:00:54,767 --> 00:00:56,633
How can you make me compete
with my children?

19
00:00:57,967 --> 00:00:59,667
On top of that, Gyeol isn't even...

20
00:00:59,667 --> 00:01:01,967
an employee of our company right now,
so what right does he have?

21
00:01:01,967 --> 00:01:03,233
Excuse me for interrupting.

22
00:01:04,000 --> 00:01:05,633
I just came to see Grandpa for a bit.

23
00:01:06,567 --> 00:01:07,833
Please exclude me, Grandpa.

24
00:01:10,067 --> 00:01:14,200
You heard him, right?
Gyeol says he just came to visit.

25
00:01:14,600 --> 00:01:15,600
Look at you.

26
00:01:16,600 --> 00:01:19,167
If I say it's happening,
that's the end of it!

27
00:01:22,867 --> 00:01:26,667
Whoever ultimately wins this race...

28
00:01:28,533 --> 00:01:30,800
will receive half of my shares.

29
00:01:32,333 --> 00:01:34,400
- Chairman!
- That's all. You may leave.

30
00:01:35,400 --> 00:01:36,467
Gyeol, stay for a moment.

31
00:01:37,333 --> 00:01:38,333
- Chairman.
- Chairman.

32
00:01:38,633 --> 00:01:40,400
Didn't you hear me tell you to leave?

33
00:01:51,533 --> 00:01:52,533
Grandpa, I...

34
00:01:52,533 --> 00:01:54,867
This is something I've been thinking about
for a long time.

35
00:01:55,833 --> 00:01:58,933
Don't argue.
Just follow your grandpa's will.

36
00:01:59,300 --> 00:02:00,467
Please reconsider.

37
00:02:00,867 --> 00:02:02,500
I have no intention of getting involved
in Kangsu Construction,

38
00:02:02,500 --> 00:02:04,000
nor am I qualified, Grandpa.

39
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:08,433
Get up. We need to go somewhere.

40
00:02:11,200 --> 00:02:13,700
Does this even make any sense?

41
00:02:14,100 --> 00:02:16,200
Compete in a succession race
with Gyeol of all people?

42
00:02:16,967 --> 00:02:19,467
I absolutely can't do it. Why should I?

43
00:02:20,900 --> 00:02:23,067
What if you can't? What if you don't?

44
00:02:24,367 --> 00:02:25,367
Father.

45
00:02:26,033 --> 00:02:29,400
Don't you know that in Kangsu Group,
your grandpa's word is law?

46
00:02:29,700 --> 00:02:31,200
Even so, this is too much.

47
00:02:32,267 --> 00:02:35,767
If you win this race,

48
00:02:36,700 --> 00:02:38,885
combined with the three percent
you currently hold,

49
00:02:38,885 --> 00:02:40,200
you'll have 23 percent.

50
00:02:40,533 --> 00:02:44,500
That means you'll have more shares
than I do, since I hold 20 percent.

51
00:02:45,233 --> 00:02:47,467
What? Then does that mean...

52
00:02:48,767 --> 00:02:50,767
I could become the chairman
of Kangsu Group?

53
00:02:51,133 --> 00:02:52,633
That's just how it works in theory.

54
00:02:53,667 --> 00:02:57,367
But if Gyeol wins this race,

55
00:02:57,667 --> 00:02:58,900
what do you think will happen?

56
00:03:00,267 --> 00:03:02,867
It means you and Gyeol
will become competitors...

57
00:03:02,867 --> 00:03:05,500
for the position of successor, right?

58
00:03:06,033 --> 00:03:08,467
Do you understand now
what kind of race this is?

59
00:03:09,367 --> 00:03:10,367
Don't worry too much.

60
00:03:10,800 --> 00:03:12,533
Even if that happens by some chance,

61
00:03:12,533 --> 00:03:14,867
if we pool my shares with Mom's shares,

62
00:03:14,867 --> 00:03:16,067
the ultimate winner will be you, Father.

63
00:03:16,500 --> 00:03:19,200
The problem is...

64
00:03:20,100 --> 00:03:22,267
who those shares will go to.
That's the issue.

65
00:03:22,633 --> 00:03:23,867
Those shares...

66
00:03:26,833 --> 00:03:28,133
Could it be Grandma?

67
00:03:28,767 --> 00:03:31,667
Your grandpa is more than capable
of doing that.

68
00:03:32,600 --> 00:03:35,033
I've lived with that old man
for over 50 years.

69
00:03:37,667 --> 00:03:38,667
What is this smell?

70
00:03:39,233 --> 00:03:41,667
Why go to all that trouble?

71
00:03:42,000 --> 00:03:44,300
You could just go to the herbal clinic
and get it made.

72
00:03:44,300 --> 00:03:45,333
It's not like this is a one-time thing.

73
00:03:45,800 --> 00:03:47,900
The whole house reeks of herbal medicine.

74
00:03:47,900 --> 00:03:49,667
I can't even breathe.

75
00:03:50,467 --> 00:03:52,433
I feel more at ease brewing it myself...

76
00:03:52,433 --> 00:03:54,567
than having someone else prepare it.

77
00:03:55,000 --> 00:03:56,067
So just put up with it.

78
00:03:56,667 --> 00:03:59,667
I don't mean to say this,

79
00:04:00,067 --> 00:04:03,233
but Father
shouldn't be taking tonics anymore.

80
00:04:03,467 --> 00:04:04,467
Don't you know?

81
00:04:04,867 --> 00:04:06,867
They say
if one takes too many good things,

82
00:04:06,867 --> 00:04:09,100
they won't pass peacefully.

83
00:04:14,400 --> 00:04:15,533
Yes, Mrs. Kang.

84
00:04:17,033 --> 00:04:18,033
Tonight?

85
00:04:18,800 --> 00:04:20,100
Not this Sunday?

86
00:04:21,467 --> 00:04:23,933
I see, the exhibition schedule.

87
00:04:24,800 --> 00:04:26,800
Then I'll check Min Ho's schedule...

88
00:04:26,800 --> 00:04:28,767
and get back to you right away. Bye.

89
00:04:30,133 --> 00:04:32,800
My goodness! It has to be today?

90
00:04:35,000 --> 00:04:37,333
If that happens,

91
00:04:37,767 --> 00:04:39,700
what kind of game does this turn into?

92
00:04:40,133 --> 00:04:42,267
Worst-case scenario,
if Gyeol wins, it's a tie with you.

93
00:04:42,733 --> 00:04:45,100
And if Grandma's shares go to Gyeol...

94
00:04:46,067 --> 00:04:47,700
Thinking about it gives me chills.

95
00:04:52,067 --> 00:04:53,067
Hi, Mom.

96
00:04:54,600 --> 00:04:57,833
I told you I'm not going on a blind date.
I don't want to!

97
00:04:57,833 --> 00:04:59,967
Whether you like it or not,
decide after you meet her.

98
00:05:00,233 --> 00:05:01,933
If you bail, you're not my son.

99
00:05:05,033 --> 00:05:06,267
Today is really not my day.

100
00:05:07,067 --> 00:05:09,533
I mean, the second daughter of Samho...

101
00:05:09,533 --> 00:05:12,200
is more than good enough for you.
Why wouldn't you meet her?

102
00:05:12,533 --> 00:05:15,133
Whether she's more than enough or not,
I said I don't want to.

103
00:05:15,533 --> 00:05:16,533
Is it because of Ms. Seo?

104
00:05:16,967 --> 00:05:18,767
You're refusing a blind date
because of Seung Ri?

105
00:05:18,900 --> 00:05:20,233
Why? Is that not allowed?

106
00:05:20,600 --> 00:05:22,367
You still haven't come to your senses,
have you?

107
00:05:23,167 --> 00:05:25,033
Of all the women out there,
you had to pick Seo Gwon Sik's daughter?

108
00:05:25,033 --> 00:05:26,033
Seriously, I ought to...

109
00:05:26,200 --> 00:05:27,200
Father!

110
00:05:27,833 --> 00:05:30,633
Why do you think I assigned Ms. Seo...

111
00:05:30,633 --> 00:05:32,433
to the Strategic Planning Division...

112
00:05:32,433 --> 00:05:35,000
out of all the departments?

113
00:05:35,000 --> 00:05:38,467
Do you think I placed her there
so you two could date?

114
00:05:38,633 --> 00:05:39,933
What are you saying?

115
00:05:39,933 --> 00:05:41,333
I'm already furious as it is.

116
00:05:41,700 --> 00:05:44,767
What do you think your strength is?

117
00:05:44,900 --> 00:05:45,900
Your strength...

118
00:05:47,733 --> 00:05:49,400
is not your brain. It's your blood.

119
00:05:49,767 --> 00:05:51,733
The only legitimate heir
of Ko Kang Su and Ko Dae Chi.

120
00:05:52,600 --> 00:05:54,833
Could you explain that more simply?

121
00:05:55,367 --> 00:05:56,367
Seung Ri...

122
00:05:57,867 --> 00:06:00,300
is a capable human resource
for you to utilize,

123
00:06:00,300 --> 00:06:01,867
not someone you marry, you brat.

124
00:06:04,133 --> 00:06:05,133
Listen carefully.

125
00:06:05,867 --> 00:06:08,233
If you lose this race to Gyeol...

126
00:06:08,233 --> 00:06:09,500
Who's going to lose?

127
00:06:10,167 --> 00:06:11,400
I might lose to others,

128
00:06:11,667 --> 00:06:14,700
but I can never lose to Gyeol.
I will never lose to him.

129
00:06:24,200 --> 00:06:25,200
Gyeol.

130
00:06:26,567 --> 00:06:27,600
Hi, Seung Ri.

131
00:06:28,546 --> 00:06:29,917
What brings you to the company?

132
00:06:30,433 --> 00:06:31,667
I came to see Grandpa.

133
00:06:35,000 --> 00:06:36,500
I heard you stopped by the house
over the weekend.

134
00:06:37,300 --> 00:06:40,667
I'm sorry I missed you.
I was taking a nap.

135
00:06:40,667 --> 00:06:41,933
Not at all, Chairman.

136
00:06:41,933 --> 00:06:45,000
I should have visited you sooner.
How have you been feeling?

137
00:06:45,800 --> 00:06:47,667
As you can see, I'm perfectly fine.

138
00:06:48,767 --> 00:06:51,667
Now that Gyeol is here too,
come visit often from now on.

139
00:06:51,933 --> 00:06:52,933
Yes, Chairman.

140
00:06:53,300 --> 00:06:54,767
- Let's go.
- Yes.

141
00:07:12,067 --> 00:07:13,100
Ms. Seo.

142
00:07:15,667 --> 00:07:17,000
Clear your schedule tonight.

143
00:07:17,000 --> 00:07:19,000
- I'm sorry, I already have plans...
- Cancel them.

144
00:07:20,800 --> 00:07:22,433
I have an important buyer meeting,

145
00:07:22,867 --> 00:07:25,367
and since I'm not good at English,
I'd like you to interpret.

146
00:07:25,933 --> 00:07:27,200
Yes, understood.

147
00:07:32,233 --> 00:07:34,967
What? Eun Ae has what?

148
00:07:36,567 --> 00:07:39,200
A baby.

149
00:07:39,833 --> 00:07:41,733
The child she gave birth to.

150
00:07:42,067 --> 00:07:45,433
Ma'am, are you still half asleep?

151
00:07:45,433 --> 00:07:47,567
Or did the early heat get to you?

152
00:07:48,333 --> 00:07:50,867
My goodness, this is so frustrating.

153
00:07:51,100 --> 00:07:54,233
At first, I thought I must've misheard,

154
00:07:54,233 --> 00:07:55,667
but I didn't.

155
00:07:56,267 --> 00:07:58,733
I heard it clearly with my own two ears.

156
00:07:58,733 --> 00:08:02,767
She said she would never give up
the child she gave birth to.

157
00:08:03,967 --> 00:08:06,333
I think it's a daughter...

158
00:08:06,767 --> 00:08:07,800
- A daughter.
- What are you doing here?

159
00:08:08,267 --> 00:08:09,333
I've already ground all the mung beans.

160
00:08:09,333 --> 00:08:13,300
Okay, I was just about to leave.

161
00:08:15,267 --> 00:08:17,133
Don't take my words lightly, okay?

162
00:08:18,300 --> 00:08:20,667
Okay?

163
00:08:28,000 --> 00:08:30,267
Did my grandma say something strange?

164
00:08:30,267 --> 00:08:32,800
Yes. She said Eun Ae has a secret child.

165
00:08:32,800 --> 00:08:36,100
This is insane.
I told her that's not true.

166
00:08:37,933 --> 00:08:39,100
Anyway, Cho Rong,

167
00:08:40,100 --> 00:08:43,533
I heard Eun Ae broke up with that senior.

168
00:08:43,933 --> 00:08:45,300
What on earth happened?

169
00:08:45,300 --> 00:08:47,367
You already heard?

170
00:08:47,367 --> 00:08:49,967
She told me herself yesterday
that they broke up.

171
00:08:51,100 --> 00:08:53,800
So I'm thinking
of meeting that guy myself.

172
00:08:54,233 --> 00:08:57,667
What? They've already broken up,
so why meet him?

173
00:08:58,167 --> 00:09:00,367
Even though Eun Ae
can be a bit careless and naive,

174
00:09:00,367 --> 00:09:02,233
she's not the type to be that reckless.

175
00:09:02,667 --> 00:09:05,733
There must be another reason.

176
00:09:06,733 --> 00:09:09,833
I'm going to go to Eun Ae's office now,
so don't say anything to her.

177
00:09:10,000 --> 00:09:11,867
What? Her office?

178
00:09:12,467 --> 00:09:14,833
Just hang in there. I'll get you out soon.

179
00:09:15,733 --> 00:09:19,667
Let's take back the company
and fight until the end together.

180
00:09:24,367 --> 00:09:25,367
Hey, Cho Rong.

181
00:09:26,467 --> 00:09:27,733
What? Mom?

182
00:09:29,767 --> 00:09:32,667
I'll be there in 30 minutes,
so hold Mom back, okay?

183
00:09:34,600 --> 00:09:35,900
This is driving me crazy.

184
00:09:47,933 --> 00:09:50,200
My stomach!

185
00:09:50,833 --> 00:09:52,600
What's wrong?
What's with your stomach all of a sudden?

186
00:09:52,933 --> 00:09:54,100
I don't know.

187
00:09:54,667 --> 00:09:56,033
I think I got indigestion from breakfast.

188
00:09:56,933 --> 00:10:00,033
My stomach's all knotted up,
and I can hardly breathe.

189
00:10:00,600 --> 00:10:02,533
This is bad.
Do you want some digestive medicine?

190
00:10:04,267 --> 00:10:05,267
I'm dying.

191
00:10:07,933 --> 00:10:10,100
Rather than medicine,

192
00:10:10,300 --> 00:10:13,200
I think it'll be quicker
if you prick my finger.

193
00:10:13,933 --> 00:10:15,233
Prick your finger?

194
00:10:18,667 --> 00:10:19,667
What's wrong, Cho Rong?

195
00:10:19,667 --> 00:10:21,833
She says she got indigestion
from breakfast,

196
00:10:22,400 --> 00:10:23,700
so take a look at her.

197
00:10:23,900 --> 00:10:25,667
How am I supposed to examine her?

198
00:10:25,667 --> 00:10:28,767
Are you in a lot of pain?
What hurts and how?

199
00:10:28,767 --> 00:10:31,767
It's just indigestion.
Go to school already.

200
00:10:32,967 --> 00:10:34,233
What do we do? Hey.

201
00:10:34,233 --> 00:10:36,233
Go get the sewing kit over there.

202
00:10:36,233 --> 00:10:37,667
- Hurry.
- Okay.

203
00:10:37,667 --> 00:10:38,933
Hey...

204
00:10:38,933 --> 00:10:39,933
Here.

205
00:10:40,100 --> 00:10:42,967
Then disinfect the needle first.

206
00:10:42,967 --> 00:10:44,033
Disinfect?

207
00:10:46,533 --> 00:10:47,533
What do we do?

208
00:10:53,767 --> 00:10:55,600
It's been a long time
since I've pricked a finger.

209
00:10:56,700 --> 00:10:57,800
Dr. Cho, you do it.

210
00:10:57,800 --> 00:10:58,867
How can I?

211
00:10:59,533 --> 00:11:00,700
I can't do things like that.

212
00:11:00,700 --> 00:11:01,933
Why not? Just think of it...

213
00:11:01,933 --> 00:11:04,500
as giving a patient an injection,
and poke her finger.

214
00:11:04,800 --> 00:11:06,833
You're surely better than me
since you're a doctor. Hurry.

215
00:11:06,833 --> 00:11:08,500
No, I'm not a doctor.

216
00:11:09,000 --> 00:11:10,767
And if you do things like this recklessly,

217
00:11:10,767 --> 00:11:11,767
it's a violation
of the Medical Service Act.

218
00:11:12,167 --> 00:11:14,267
Medical Service Act, my foot. Hurry up!

219
00:11:15,500 --> 00:11:16,533
Quick, prick it.

220
00:11:26,033 --> 00:11:28,133
- What do we do?
- I'm sorry.

221
00:11:28,133 --> 00:11:30,600
I really can't do it. Mom, you do it.

222
00:11:31,633 --> 00:11:33,700
You're a doctor,
yet you can't even prick a finger...

223
00:11:34,867 --> 00:11:35,867
Come here.

224
00:11:39,800 --> 00:11:40,867
Why are you so startled?

225
00:11:40,867 --> 00:11:43,400
How are you going to handle patients
in the future like that?

226
00:11:44,000 --> 00:11:46,667
Right, I'll be off then.

227
00:11:47,433 --> 00:11:48,533
Seriously.

228
00:11:48,867 --> 00:11:50,600
How is it? Does it feel a bit better?

229
00:11:51,067 --> 00:11:52,733
Yes, just a little.

230
00:11:54,000 --> 00:11:55,800
- Seriously.
- Why isn't she coming?

231
00:11:57,033 --> 00:11:59,067
Ma'am, just one more time.

232
00:12:02,133 --> 00:12:03,167
One more time?

233
00:12:10,467 --> 00:12:11,500
Eun Ae.

234
00:12:13,300 --> 00:12:15,567
What brings you here?
You're in the middle of your workday.

235
00:12:16,100 --> 00:12:19,333
I'm going to work from home today.

236
00:12:19,633 --> 00:12:20,633
Work from home?

237
00:12:22,267 --> 00:12:25,267
Why? Because it's uncomfortable
sharing an office with that senior?

238
00:12:25,333 --> 00:12:27,433
Not exactly.

239
00:12:28,467 --> 00:12:31,167
Give me his contact information.

240
00:12:32,233 --> 00:12:33,333
Why do you need his contact information?

241
00:12:33,333 --> 00:12:35,500
You two barely started dating,
and you already broke up.

242
00:12:35,500 --> 00:12:37,100
I'm going to ask him why.

243
00:12:37,533 --> 00:12:39,500
Why would you ask him that?

244
00:12:40,500 --> 00:12:42,900
I just dumped him.

245
00:12:43,433 --> 00:12:44,533
You dumped him?

246
00:12:44,900 --> 00:12:48,667
Yes. When I had a crush,
I felt butterflies,

247
00:12:49,200 --> 00:12:51,600
but once we actually started dating,
it just didn't feel right.

248
00:12:53,067 --> 00:12:54,200
Because you didn't feel butterflies?

249
00:12:55,467 --> 00:12:57,267
"Right, that happens."

250
00:12:57,267 --> 00:12:58,300
You thought I'd say that, right?

251
00:12:59,700 --> 00:13:00,733
Be honest with me.

252
00:13:00,733 --> 00:13:03,733
Otherwise, I'll meet that guy myself
and ask him everything.

253
00:13:03,900 --> 00:13:05,033
Please.

254
00:13:05,967 --> 00:13:09,267
Since when were you so interested
in my life?

255
00:13:09,700 --> 00:13:10,700
What?

256
00:13:18,100 --> 00:13:19,100
Hello.

257
00:13:20,267 --> 00:13:23,200
You're looking for a monthly rental?
Yes, I'll be there soon.

258
00:13:24,067 --> 00:13:25,967
It seems like you have a customer.
You should go quickly.

259
00:13:28,000 --> 00:13:29,700
Cho Rong, are you okay now?

260
00:13:29,700 --> 00:13:32,300
Yes, it suddenly got much better.

261
00:13:32,633 --> 00:13:34,767
- Thank you.
- That's a relief.

262
00:13:39,267 --> 00:13:40,400
This is the very apartment...

263
00:13:41,333 --> 00:13:45,533
your father designed 25 years ago.

264
00:13:46,800 --> 00:13:49,400
Other apartments built
around the same time...

265
00:13:50,400 --> 00:13:53,200
are already being considered
for redevelopment or reconstruction,

266
00:13:54,933 --> 00:13:58,133
but this one remains solid,
without any defects.

267
00:13:59,500 --> 00:14:02,333
This apartment is a symbol
of Kangsu Construction.

268
00:14:02,600 --> 00:14:04,400
I used to come here often with my dad.

269
00:14:05,600 --> 00:14:08,620
I used to play
at that playground over there.

270
00:14:09,867 --> 00:14:11,733
It's still there.

271
00:14:24,267 --> 00:14:26,533
If your father were still alive,

272
00:14:27,367 --> 00:14:29,367
he would have become my right-hand man
by now.

273
00:14:30,967 --> 00:14:34,033
He was exceptionally capable,
deeply devoted to the company,

274
00:14:34,467 --> 00:14:39,600
and more upright and trustworthy
than anyone else. He was one of my people.

275
00:14:43,600 --> 00:14:46,900
Now you take your father's place.

276
00:14:48,600 --> 00:14:52,156
No, the dream
your father couldn't fulfill...

277
00:14:52,833 --> 00:14:54,033
you make it come true.

278
00:14:55,400 --> 00:14:58,833
Grandpa, I'll return to where I belong.

279
00:14:59,633 --> 00:15:02,267
I have no intention of competing
with Father or Min Ho.

280
00:15:02,367 --> 00:15:03,567
Who said anything about competing?

281
00:15:04,233 --> 00:15:06,233
I'm telling you
to show what you're capable of.

282
00:15:06,833 --> 00:15:09,200
There's so much you can do here.

283
00:15:09,500 --> 00:15:11,700
So why wander around in a foreign land?

284
00:15:12,033 --> 00:15:15,133
I didn't wander.
I've only just settled down.

285
00:15:17,500 --> 00:15:19,067
I don't need to hear it. I already know...

286
00:15:20,333 --> 00:15:22,333
why you left Korea.

287
00:15:25,500 --> 00:15:27,133
With the little time I have left,

288
00:15:27,800 --> 00:15:31,833
I intend to set everything back
in its place.

289
00:15:32,267 --> 00:15:33,267
Grandpa.

290
00:15:40,100 --> 00:15:44,900
You said you wouldn't forget
the moment I held your hand, right?

291
00:15:46,767 --> 00:15:49,667
This time, you hold mine.

292
00:15:50,967 --> 00:15:53,467
It's your grandpa's last request.

293
00:16:06,233 --> 00:16:08,667
Grandpa!

294
00:16:08,667 --> 00:16:10,467
Grandpa, are you okay? Grandpa!

295
00:16:11,200 --> 00:16:13,333
(Haedeul Hospital)

296
00:16:14,600 --> 00:16:18,233
It has metastasized to the brain,
lymph nodes, and liver,

297
00:16:18,767 --> 00:16:20,364
so further treatment is meaningless.

298
00:16:21,467 --> 00:16:23,933
The Chairman knows this
and has chosen to give up.

299
00:16:24,133 --> 00:16:27,210
Are you saying
there's no possible treatment?

300
00:16:28,133 --> 00:16:30,103
Unfortunately, at this point,

301
00:16:30,567 --> 00:16:34,687
he has at most one to two years,
or as little as six months left.

302
00:16:44,183 --> 00:16:45,636
Chairman!

303
00:16:47,333 --> 00:16:48,600
- Hello.
- What happened?

304
00:16:48,967 --> 00:16:50,695
He was perfectly fine this morning.

305
00:16:52,300 --> 00:16:54,058
What did you do to him?

306
00:16:54,058 --> 00:16:55,433
What are you talking about?

307
00:16:55,667 --> 00:16:58,722
Are you saying the Chairman collapsed
because of Gyeol?

308
00:16:59,600 --> 00:17:01,791
Why is it so noisy?

309
00:17:02,667 --> 00:17:05,042
Father, are you feeling alright?

310
00:17:09,467 --> 00:17:13,396
I'm fine now, so you should go.

311
00:17:15,300 --> 00:17:16,600
Didn't you hear him?

312
00:17:21,467 --> 00:17:22,556
I'll take my leave now.

313
00:17:27,167 --> 00:17:30,039
I'll go and bring Dr. Kim.

314
00:17:32,667 --> 00:17:34,933
Your 60th birthday is approaching,

315
00:17:35,933 --> 00:17:38,067
yet you never change.

316
00:17:38,800 --> 00:17:39,900
Father.

317
00:17:39,900 --> 00:17:42,100
When I said I'd adopt him as my son,

318
00:17:43,133 --> 00:17:44,810
you were the first to step forward.

319
00:17:46,233 --> 00:17:48,367
Then you should act like a proper father.

320
00:17:49,642 --> 00:17:51,098
How much longer...

321
00:17:51,098 --> 00:17:54,282
I've done my part.
What more do you expect from me?

322
00:17:59,167 --> 00:18:00,567
Min Ho was going to come as well,

323
00:18:00,567 --> 00:18:02,946
but he has an important blind date today.

324
00:18:03,167 --> 00:18:05,333
- As soon as it's over...
- No need to come.

325
00:18:06,000 --> 00:18:09,233
I'll be discharged tomorrow.
Don't make a fuss.

326
00:18:10,800 --> 00:18:11,800
Okay.

327
00:18:13,467 --> 00:18:14,567
Well...

328
00:18:15,333 --> 00:18:17,034
She's the second daughter of Samho Group.

329
00:18:17,667 --> 00:18:19,223
If things go well,
the synergy between the two families...

330
00:18:19,500 --> 00:18:20,667
Just go.

331
00:18:22,700 --> 00:18:24,267
I need some sleep.

332
00:18:39,300 --> 00:18:41,388
- Ms. Kim So Hui?
- Yes.

333
00:18:43,267 --> 00:18:44,764
Let's sit down first.

334
00:18:50,467 --> 00:18:51,610
I'm Ko Min Ho.

335
00:18:51,967 --> 00:18:53,868
You're even more beautiful in person
than in your photos.

336
00:18:54,533 --> 00:18:58,026
Thank you. But who is this?

337
00:18:58,172 --> 00:18:59,455
Let me introduce you.

338
00:19:00,333 --> 00:19:03,039
This is my girlfriend, Seo Seung Ri.

339
00:19:03,600 --> 00:19:05,274
- Sorry?
- Director.

340
00:19:05,274 --> 00:19:08,300
I couldn't just stand up
a meeting arranged by my mother,

341
00:19:08,533 --> 00:19:11,767
but I also couldn't betray my girlfriend,

342
00:19:12,200 --> 00:19:13,500
so I brought her along like this.

343
00:19:14,667 --> 00:19:17,267
What did you say? That's insane.

344
00:19:24,867 --> 00:19:25,900
Hey, Seo Seung Ri.

345
00:19:26,722 --> 00:19:28,200
Isn't this too much?

346
00:19:31,467 --> 00:19:33,719
You should've let her do it.

347
00:19:34,833 --> 00:19:37,031
Do I look like a joke to you,
Director Ko Min Ho?

348
00:19:39,533 --> 00:19:42,767
If you pull a stunt like this again,
I won't tolerate it.

349
00:19:45,567 --> 00:19:46,567
Wait.

350
00:19:48,800 --> 00:19:50,067
What are you two doing right now?

351
00:19:50,767 --> 00:19:53,933
By tomorrow, I'll probably be blacklisted
from the blind date market.

352
00:19:54,167 --> 00:19:55,200
That's exactly my goal.

353
00:19:56,333 --> 00:19:57,800
I'm truly sorry, Ms. Kim So Hui.

354
00:19:57,800 --> 00:19:59,033
Hey, Mr. Ko Min Ho.

355
00:19:59,033 --> 00:20:00,100
I'll buy you a drink later.

356
00:20:00,100 --> 00:20:01,867
So please spread the word far and wide...

357
00:20:02,067 --> 00:20:04,539
that Ko Min Ho of Kangsu Construction
is completely insane.

358
00:20:04,539 --> 00:20:05,539
Bye then.

359
00:20:20,133 --> 00:20:21,564
Give it here, I'll do it for you.

360
00:20:21,674 --> 00:20:22,967
Here.

361
00:20:23,533 --> 00:20:26,067
You've been using pain relief patches
quite often lately.

362
00:20:26,600 --> 00:20:28,930
For someone who just sits in meetings
and gets approvals,

363
00:20:28,930 --> 00:20:30,372
what do you need your shoulders for?

364
00:20:31,000 --> 00:20:32,836
- Here?
- Yeah, there.

365
00:20:33,067 --> 00:20:34,938
No, a bit lower.

366
00:20:35,733 --> 00:20:37,200
- Is it frozen shoulder?
- There.

367
00:20:38,911 --> 00:20:40,828
- Good.
- All done.

368
00:20:47,500 --> 00:20:48,700
That's strange.

369
00:20:49,400 --> 00:20:53,200
Why do I keep smelling disinfectant
on you lately?

370
00:20:54,667 --> 00:20:56,100
Disinfectant?

371
00:20:58,233 --> 00:21:00,700
What are you talking about?
I just took a shower.

372
00:21:01,767 --> 00:21:03,533
Have you secretly...

373
00:21:06,167 --> 00:21:07,167
been going to the swimming pool?

374
00:21:09,467 --> 00:21:12,300
The indoor pool has a similar smell.

375
00:21:12,967 --> 00:21:14,439
Don't be ridiculous.

376
00:21:14,867 --> 00:21:17,178
When would I have time to go swimming?

377
00:21:19,588 --> 00:21:20,633
Is that so?

378
00:21:24,772 --> 00:21:25,800
About Eun Ae...

379
00:21:27,533 --> 00:21:29,122
I think she really broke up.

380
00:21:32,133 --> 00:21:33,900
She still hasn't told you why?

381
00:21:34,800 --> 00:21:38,815
She says she dumped him or something,

382
00:21:40,000 --> 00:21:43,754
but how are they
supposed to work together now?

383
00:21:45,133 --> 00:21:49,260
More than that,

384
00:21:49,800 --> 00:21:50,933
I'm worried she might be hurt.

385
00:21:53,000 --> 00:21:55,484
I guess things in life
don't always go the way you want.

386
00:21:56,860 --> 00:21:58,855
For you, Eun Hyeong, and Eun Nim,

387
00:21:59,212 --> 00:22:02,428
everything just seems to work out.

388
00:22:03,300 --> 00:22:04,333
Go to sleep already.

389
00:22:05,367 --> 00:22:06,367
Okay.

390
00:22:13,267 --> 00:22:16,433
You said you wouldn't forget...

391
00:22:17,333 --> 00:22:18,800
the moment I held your hand, right?

392
00:22:20,767 --> 00:22:23,800
This time, you hold mine.

393
00:22:25,167 --> 00:22:28,200
It's your grandpa's last request.

394
00:22:35,333 --> 00:22:36,333
You're late.

395
00:22:38,033 --> 00:22:39,033
Did you drink?

396
00:22:39,367 --> 00:22:41,300
Yeah, I had a drink.

397
00:22:49,267 --> 00:22:50,400
What are you doing here?

398
00:22:51,133 --> 00:22:53,533
I just like the night breeze.

399
00:22:54,800 --> 00:22:56,467
Night breeze, my foot.

400
00:23:00,967 --> 00:23:02,082
You know,

401
00:23:04,067 --> 00:23:07,167
I really hate you. Then and now.

402
00:23:08,000 --> 00:23:10,067
You just lay your feelings out like that.

403
00:23:10,733 --> 00:23:12,133
There's no need to say it out loud.
We all know.

404
00:23:13,133 --> 00:23:15,233
You've grown up, haven't you?

405
00:23:15,833 --> 00:23:17,276
Look at you, talking back.

406
00:23:25,367 --> 00:23:26,367
Do you remember?

407
00:23:27,033 --> 00:23:28,933
The first day I stepped on you.

408
00:23:35,267 --> 00:23:38,442
Min Ho, at least tell me why
before you hit me.

409
00:23:38,442 --> 00:23:39,724
You don't need to know, you bastard.

410
00:23:40,233 --> 00:23:42,633
When I hit you, you take it.
When I step on you, you get stepped on.

411
00:23:42,633 --> 00:23:45,533
Stop it already. Why are you doing this?

412
00:23:51,000 --> 00:23:52,700
That day, my homeroom teacher said...

413
00:23:53,333 --> 00:23:56,133
I should at least try to keep up
with my younger brother, Gyeol.

414
00:23:57,233 --> 00:23:59,433
That really set me off.

415
00:24:02,133 --> 00:24:05,324
But don't feel too wronged.

416
00:24:06,367 --> 00:24:07,367
That day,

417
00:24:08,567 --> 00:24:12,954
Grandpa beat me with a baseball bat
until I bled.

418
00:24:14,767 --> 00:24:16,100
That was the price for stepping on you.

419
00:24:23,100 --> 00:24:24,100
Hey.

420
00:24:25,200 --> 00:24:27,300
Don't even think about rising against me.

421
00:24:28,700 --> 00:24:32,333
Every time you try, I'll crush you.
Got that?

422
00:24:38,367 --> 00:24:39,600
About that race.

423
00:24:44,033 --> 00:24:46,300
I wasn't planning to get involved...

424
00:24:50,033 --> 00:24:51,900
- but I've changed my mind.
- What?

425
00:24:54,200 --> 00:24:57,500
Are you challenging me right now?

426
00:25:00,167 --> 00:25:01,300
Challenge?

427
00:25:02,200 --> 00:25:06,200
I'll just take it easy. Real easy.

428
00:25:21,267 --> 00:25:22,867
(Kangsu Construction)

429
00:25:22,867 --> 00:25:24,033
A retirement community?

430
00:25:24,767 --> 00:25:26,500
You already know that my final wish...

431
00:25:27,833 --> 00:25:31,364
is to build a retirement community
through Kangsu Construction.

432
00:25:33,600 --> 00:25:37,567
That retirement community
is your task for this race.

433
00:25:37,567 --> 00:25:39,467
Wait, Chairman.

434
00:25:40,133 --> 00:25:43,698
That retirement community project
has already been finalized...

435
00:25:43,698 --> 00:25:45,562
I am the final decision-maker.

436
00:25:46,567 --> 00:25:48,033
And I haven't approved it yet.

437
00:25:49,800 --> 00:25:51,367
Form a retirement community TF.

438
00:25:52,967 --> 00:25:53,967
Team 1, Ko Min Ho.

439
00:25:56,200 --> 00:25:57,700
Team 2, Ko Gyeol.

440
00:25:58,500 --> 00:26:01,996
Then what about me?
What is my role in this race?

441
00:26:02,333 --> 00:26:05,362
No matter how hard I try to understand,

442
00:26:05,362 --> 00:26:07,138
I just can't make sense of this, Chairman.

443
00:26:07,567 --> 00:26:12,044
President Ko will fairly supervise
and manage both teams.

444
00:26:12,951 --> 00:26:16,151
If I catch even the slightest unfairness,

445
00:26:16,151 --> 00:26:18,867
you'll be eliminated
from the race immediately.

446
00:26:19,800 --> 00:26:20,867
Chairman.

447
00:26:20,867 --> 00:26:22,812
For a CEO,

448
00:26:22,812 --> 00:26:25,400
the most important thing
is management ability.

449
00:26:25,967 --> 00:26:28,033
Yes, I understand.

450
00:26:28,567 --> 00:26:30,815
I have one question.

451
00:26:32,067 --> 00:26:35,433
What kind of retirement community
do you want, Chairman?

452
00:26:37,167 --> 00:26:39,100
Don't overthink it.

453
00:26:41,067 --> 00:26:44,967
A home I want to live in
for the rest of my life,

454
00:26:46,967 --> 00:26:49,733
a home I want to live in
until my last breath.

455
00:26:52,033 --> 00:26:53,033
My home.

456
00:26:58,367 --> 00:27:00,000
(Kangsu Construction)

457
00:27:00,000 --> 00:27:03,133
Kangsu Construction's CPO
contacted me a while ago.

458
00:27:03,733 --> 00:27:06,455
He said our program was interesting
and wanted to acquire it.

459
00:27:08,467 --> 00:27:12,567
It was the CPO who led the acquisition?

460
00:27:19,333 --> 00:27:21,433
I'm here to meet
the Chief Planning Officer.

461
00:27:21,433 --> 00:27:22,642
Where should I go?

462
00:27:22,642 --> 00:27:23,733
Do you have an appointment?

463
00:27:25,267 --> 00:27:26,933
No, I don't.

464
00:27:27,933 --> 00:27:30,596
Tell him I'm the co-CEO of Lucky Joy Tech,
he'll know.

465
00:27:30,596 --> 00:27:31,600
That's not allowed under our policy.

466
00:27:31,800 --> 00:27:33,559
You need to schedule a meeting first.

467
00:27:34,233 --> 00:27:36,167
I don't have his contact information.

468
00:27:36,167 --> 00:27:38,233
Then could you at least call him
on the intercom?

469
00:27:38,233 --> 00:27:39,500
Please?

470
00:27:39,500 --> 00:27:40,970
I said it's not allowed under our policy.

471
00:27:40,970 --> 00:27:43,828
Please, I really need to meet him.

472
00:27:43,828 --> 00:27:45,844
- You cannot.
- How can I meet him then?

473
00:27:46,200 --> 00:27:47,467
- You must have a lot of time.
- I need to talk to him.

474
00:27:47,467 --> 00:27:48,852
- Excuse me?
- I said that's not allowed.

475
00:27:49,033 --> 00:27:50,533
Can't you see
an outsider causing a disturbance?

476
00:27:50,533 --> 00:27:52,810
- You cannot.
- Is there any way at all?

477
00:27:53,067 --> 00:27:54,533
Isn't it the security team's job
to stop that?

478
00:27:54,533 --> 00:27:55,733
I said that's not allowed.

479
00:27:55,733 --> 00:27:57,436
- Yes, sir.
- I really have something to say.

480
00:27:57,967 --> 00:28:00,267
Could you please call him on the intercom?

481
00:28:00,267 --> 00:28:02,467
- It's not allowed.
- Just once, please.

482
00:28:02,467 --> 00:28:03,667
You can't do this.

483
00:28:04,100 --> 00:28:05,100
- Come out.
- What are you doing?

484
00:28:05,100 --> 00:28:06,600
I just want to meet the CPO.

485
00:28:06,600 --> 00:28:08,300
Why are you doing this? My goodness.

486
00:28:10,033 --> 00:28:12,267
He'll know me
if you say Lucky Joy Tech co-CEO.

487
00:28:12,267 --> 00:28:13,514
Lucky Joy!

488
00:28:14,267 --> 00:28:16,367
- Why are you doing this?
- Lucky Joy?

489
00:28:43,533 --> 00:28:46,000
(Our Happy Days)

490
00:28:46,267 --> 00:28:47,410
Kangsu Construction, wake up!

491
00:28:47,410 --> 00:28:49,743
I have to talk
to the Chief Planning Officer!

492
00:28:51,467 --> 00:28:52,500
Are you two-timing?

493
00:28:53,100 --> 00:28:55,833
Are you weighing your options
between Min Ho and Gyeol?

494
00:28:55,833 --> 00:28:56,867
Ma'am.

495
00:28:57,000 --> 00:29:00,600
Looks like it's almost time for me
to leave this place as well.

496
00:29:01,000 --> 00:29:04,468
Excuse me, is anyone inside?

497
00:29:05,067 --> 00:29:06,100
Excuse me.

498
00:29:06,600 --> 00:29:07,833
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
